<br>
The Kunark dragons are the next step up from Nagafen/Vox.  Sure, there are lots of other things to do from level 55 to 60 (Kael arena, blah blah blah), but a lot of raiding techniques are learned at that point (dealing with different AE's (Gore, Tal), unique procs and aggro management (VS), mob positioning (Trak)...<br>
<br>
I'd hate to see a big gap in raiding experience for players from 52 to 60.  Those players need these Kunark mobs to hone their raiding skills so they aren't complete eejits when they hit Velious and Luclin.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I don't really think manaburners are doing anything wrong (as long as they don't walk over another raid to do it).  They're using what they have, and probably having a heck of a good time doing it.  It's another case of &quot;Blame the game, not the player.&quot; <p><font size=2 color=#5555FF face="Garamond"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3474" style="text-decoration:none">King Hwedung Hightower</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/23/02 4:43:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12467.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Corruption of Mana Burn</span><hr size=1> If you want to discuss manaburn nerfs, I'd suggest you think about having it fully resisted on any 60+ mob with more than 75% of its hps remaining.<br>
